Package org.wildfly.security.auth.principal

The principal types used by this API.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnonymousPrincipal
    The singleton anonymous principal.
    CompositePrincipal
    A composite principal that consists of multiple elements of possibly disparate type.
    NamePrincipal
    A principal which is comprised of a simple String name.
    NumericPrincipal
    A principal which is represented by a numeric ID, such as what a database might use for a primary key.
    RealmNestedPrincipal
    A principal type which is used to find a specific identity in a specific realm.

Package org.wildfly.security.auth.principal Description

The principal types used by this API. Note that, as a matter of policy, principal types are defined by format (e.g. plain string, X.500 string, etc.), not by usage (e.g. user name, host name).
